Our mycophile of the week, Jakobien van der Weijden of @microdosinginstitute and yours truly @jasperiuss share an epic conversation on the different approaches and substances in the microdosing world.

I'm always beyond stoked to connect with fellow Dutch landers changing the world and Jakobien and her business partner Hein are grade A human beings and psychonauts👨‍🚀

I dropped out because of a dead battery at the end but all is saved by the team of @microdosinginstitute who showed us there is such a thing as the live archives!🧠

🍄❤️🍄❤️🍄

node.text:
Oh man, it doesn't happen often that @jasperiuss feels like he just got started with the conversation and BAM an hour is over🤯

@alex_dorr is such an energetic, humble, charismatic, simply amazing human being. (He's also really handsome 😜) His love for fungi goes through all of our systems, is incredibly infectious and it feels like he has unlimited amounts to give. You do not want to miss this one!🔥

I am so humbled to receive such high praise from someone I hold in such high regard, although I know we're all incredibly busy, i know there will be some collaborations in the air.🪶🪶🪶 

FOLLOW: @alex_dorr & @mushroomrevival 

Stay Shroomie🍄💕

node.title: Humans, Mushrooms and Magic with @alex_dorr from @mushroomrevival

Join us on @charlesrootz his beautiful 298 year old family house!

Charles is a professional musician with @rootzunderground and has recently co-founded a mushroom chocolate company @patoochocolate 🔥

Charles is an all round amazing person and his passion for mushrooms and music just oozes from him. He's been generous with his time, his words and his presence during my (@jasperiuss) trip through Jamaica. 🇯🇲

These are the leaders we need in the up and coming psychedelic space. Let's all learn from his caution and epic stories❤️🍄🙌

node.title: 🍄🍫 Mushroom Chocolate, Music and Accessibility with @charlesrootz

“We know that every particle in the physical universe takes its characteristics from the pitch and pattern and overtones or it’s particular frequency, it’s singing.
Before we make music, music makes us.” -Hazrat Inayat Khan 

Today our very own Chief Creative Officer Holden Davies of @nido_films was joined by @davidsatori from @dirtwire to discuss their influence of mushrooms for their creation of Music 🎶

If you are inspired by music & mushroom, tune into this conversation all about plant medicine & the healing power of music!
.
.

Join Skye from @real_mushrooms and yours truly, @jasperiuss for a deep dive into the world of medicinal mushrooms.🍄

Skye is one of the most knowledgeable people I've had the pleasure to talk to. He generously shared what he knows about polysaccharides, triterpenes, beta-glucans and all other mushroom medicines that our Fungi allies create to nurture our bodies.💪

Skye shares his story of growing up into a mycophelic family, how he reconnected with his father's fungal vision after rediscovering the healing powers of medicinal mushrooms in his late twenties.💫

We finished with talking about new up and coming mushrooms like Phellinus linteus and Lignosus rhinocerus.🌌

follow @real_mushrooms everywhere you consume media for more medicinal Mushroom knowledge🙌

Our mycophile of the week, Jakobien van der Weijden of @microdosinginstitute and yours truly @jasperiuss share an epic conversation on the different approaches and substances in the microdosing world.

I'm always beyond stoked to connect with fellow Dutch landers changing the world and Jakobien and her business partner Hein are grade A human beings and psychonauts👨‍🚀

I dropped out because of a dead battery at the end but all is saved by the team of @microdosinginstitute who showed us there is such a thing as the live archives!🧠

🍄❤️🍄❤️🍄

#FungiAcademy is based in a small off-grid indigenous village called Tzunaná located on Lake Atitlán in Guatemala 🇬🇹

We are partnering up with @wellkind_guatemala to support their continued ecological restoration, improving food security, and cultural preservation in Tzununa. 

Right now every dollar donated to this project will be matched by One Day’s Wages for a total grant of $31,050. This Fundraiser will end on August 31st, so we are asking for your help now! 

@well.kind reforestation project has planted over 14,000 trees in Tzununa and surrounding areas. 40% of trees planted are native fruit trees which provide forests and drought-resistant firewood (tropical ash, Central American walnut, etc.) Another 40% of trees are fruit trees to be irrigated closer to the homes of tree planters (elderberry, avocado, etc.) 15-20% of trees planted are species ideal for wetland restoration and reforestation (willow, cypress, etc.).

Head over to the link in our bio 🌿WellKind 🌿 to help support this initiative 💚
.

node.text:
Did you know that mushrooms love lightning?🌩️

Lightning strikes can more than double the amount of mushrooms coming up according to some research that's being done in Japan 🗾

Lightning makes mushrooms more plentiful, this new research offers a solid scientific basis for an ancient Japanese farmer's tale. 🧙‍♂️

Mushrooms react best when exposed to a second burst of electricity at a range of 50-100,000 volts, that causes mushrooms to give themselves a reproductive boost and increase the number of fruiting bodies so their chance of survival would maximized.⚡⚡⚡

Oh man, it doesn't happen often that @jasperiuss feels like he just got started with the conversation and BAM an hour is over🤯

@alex_dorr is such an energetic, humble, charismatic, simply amazing human being. (He's also really handsome 😜) His love for fungi goes through all of our systems, is incredibly infectious and it feels like he has unlimited amounts to give. You do not want to miss this one!🔥

I am so humbled to receive such high praise from someone I hold in such high regard, although I know we're all incredibly busy, i know there will be some collaborations in the air.🪶🪶🪶 

FOLLOW: @alex_dorr & @mushroomrevival 

Stay Shroomie🍄💕

One year later… what a journey! #HappyAnniversary 🎉

Exactly one year ago we launched our online Sacred Mycology School 🙌

It was during a time when the world went in complete lockdown and we were unable to teach our in-person courses anymore, which was the main source of our income. The day we opened up our doors to presale the course our electricity was shut off and we managed to get it back on with the help of our first few students in our Sacred Mycology School, so thank you fungi fam! 🙏

“It was divine timing” Oliver would say. And it truly was. 💫

The world needed this now more than ever. To be able to learn how to safely grow, use, and integrate all kinds of mushrooms in the comfort of their homes; whether that be for medicinal benefits, edibility consumption, psychedelic exploration, or environment restoration.

In honor of our anniversary we want to gift our community 50% off all our Sacred Mycology Courses! 🔥

Start your journey now, link in our @fungiacademy bio! 🍄
.

Want to give your crush a bouquet of your homegrown mushroom flush? 🤗

Oyster Mushrooms (Pleurotus Ostreatus) are a newbie grower's best friend when it comes to cultivation. They are one of the easiest mushrooms to grow as they can enjoy a wide variety of substrates like corn cobs, sawdust, coffee grounds, straw, cardboard, and many others! 🌿

These edible mushrooms are not just delicious edible mushrooms but do wonders for your health. Oyster Mushrooms are rich in protein, vitamin C, and potassium. They also can support the immune system, blood sugar regulation, cardiovascular conditions, skin problems, and brain health. 

🍄 Fungi Facts 🍄 Was first cultivated in Germany to help feed people during World World I. It received its name "Oyster Mushroom" due to the fact that the caps look like oysters (as you can tell from this photo from @freshcapmushrooms! 🦪

Want to learn how to grow your own Oyster Mushrooms? Click the link in our @fungiacademy bio to sign up for our newsletter 💌 
We have some exciting news releasing tomorrow so you can start growing mushrooms with a shweeet deal! 💫
